  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Mental Health Care and Forensic Psychological Evidence Collection in Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">47% of women and girls in Kenya have suffered physical or sexual violence, a figure that rises in times of conflict. At least 900 people were sexually violated in the unrest following Kenya&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;s 2007 national election. Victims faced stigma, a lack of mental health services, and weak police and justice systems. Many crimes were not reported. Cases that made it to court often failed due to lack of robust evidence. PHR Kenya works to improve the collection and use of forensic evidence to better support victims of sexual crimes. This project will extend their work to improve collection of psychological evidence to support legal cases, and help survivors of sexual violence get mental health care.</narrative>
  </description>
